The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 June is 42,973 (4,973.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 June, there were 287 new confirmed cases (33.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 June, there were 227 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 26% (60 extra cases).
